    "about": "Healthcare for All and Cities for People\n\nI am a designer at heart and find joy in reconfiguring systems so that wellbeing is built into the way we live. As a Special Ops Analyst on MedGrocer’s Population Health team, I lead innovation and capacity-building initiatives that strengthen healthcare for over 20,000 patients, testing first-of-kind models that inform the future of healthcare delivery in the country. \n\nAt Duke University and Duke Kunshan University, I specialized in computational research across labs in U.S. and China that aim to reduce inequality in the Global South. These projects spanned co-developing antibiotic alternatives to combat drug-resistant infections, examining the effects of lesser studied product additives on coastal populations, and evaluating the impact of digital health tools. \n\nBeyond the clinical, I see wellbeing as a relational practice that emerges in the co-creation of space and culture. At Branch Out for Justice, I interviewed feminist leaders to document movement-building across Latin America. As the Lead of Young Urbanists Philippines, I implement platforms and programming that empower youth to advocate for inclusive planning education and youth-led tactical interventions within their cities. \n\nAcross organizational, biological, and urban systems, I see capacity-building—and by extension, self-making—as the art of understanding disparate parts and rewiring them into interconnected strengths, by design.",
